Prices of selected food items continued the upward trend in May, according to the National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) in its Selected Food Prices Watch Report for May released in Abuja on Wednesday. The NBS said the average price of 1kg of white beans rose on a year-on-year basis by 37.22 per cent from N382.37 in May 2021 to N524.70 in May 2022. On a month-on-month basis, it increased by 1.09 per cent from N519.05 in April to N524.70 in May. According to the report, the average price of 1kg of a yam tuber increased on a year-on-year basis by 37.87 per cent from N269.98 in May 2021 to N372.23 in May 2022. On a month-on-month basis, the average price of yam increased by 3.05 per cent in May 2022, compared to what was obtained in April. In the same vein, the average price of 2kg pre-packed wheat flour rose by 34.92 per cent on a year-on-year basis from the value recorded in May 2021 at N785.87 to N1,060.26 in May 2022. On a month-on-month basis, it increased from N1,047.74 in April  to N1,060.26 in May 2022 indicating a 1.20 per cent rise,. The NBS further stated that the average price of a bottle of palm oil increased by 42.81 per cent from N593.36 in May 2021 to N847.39 in May 2022. On a month-on-month basis, It also rose by 0.55 per cent between APRIL and May. It nited that the average price of 1kg of boneless beef rose by 34.11 per cent on a year-on-year basis from N1,513.43 in May 2021 to N 2,029.59 in May 2022. Also, it rose by 0.55 per cent on a month-on-month basis between APRIL and May. According to the report, the average price of 1kg of boneless beef rose by 34.11 per cent on a year-on-year basis from N1,513.43 in May 2021 to N 2,029.59 in May 2022. It added that the average price of one bottle of groundnut oil stood at N1,040.88 in May 2022, showing an increase of 47.99 per cent compared to N703.36 in May 2021, and add: “on a month-on-month basis, it rose by 3.29 per cent from N 1,007.68 in April 2022″. ALSO READ FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE  The report states that Ebonyi State recorded the highest average price of white beans at N899.79 for 1kg, while the lowest was reported in Borno at N262.79. The NBS stated that the highest average price of 1kg of a yam tuber was recorded in Akwa-Ibom at N804.45, while the lowest was recorded in Bauchi at N134.17, noting that Abia recorded the highest price of 2kg pre-packaged wheat flour at N1,393, while Yobe recorded the lowest price at N755.03. The NBS in its zone by zone analysis said that the South-East recorded the highest average price of brown beans at N834.93 per kilogramme, followed by the South-West at N579.06 per kilogramme, while the North-East recorded the least with N295.20. Following a similar pattern, the South-West recorded the highest price of average yam tuber at N535.27, followed by the South-South with N450.12, while the lowest was recorded in the Northeast at N141.10. It said that the average price of 2kg pre-packaged wheat flour was higher in the South-East and the South-West at N1,332.34 and N1,116.38, respectively, stressing that “the lowest price for pre-packaged wheat flour was recorded in the Northeast at N810.23.” 